name: VMWARE ESXI 8.X - Content Pack
summary: Content pack containing Dashboards and parsed security events only

source.@value:
pipeline "SYSLOG - VMWare - ESXI"
stage 0 match either
rule "Syslog - VMWARE - log_level lookup"
stage 1 match pass
rule "Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - Extract SSH info"
stage 4 match either
rule "Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - Extract vmw_esxi_title & vmw_esxi_info_message"
stage 5 match either
rule "Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - vmw_esxi_title - Extract key/value pair"
stage 6 match either
rule "Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - vmw_esxi_info_message - Extract data"
stage 2 match pass
rule "Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - Extract Shell info"
end

source.@value:
rule "Syslog - VMWARE - log_level lookup"

when
  has_field("level")
  then
   let new_level_severity = lookup_value("rfc_log_level", to_string($message.level));
   set_field("level_severity", new_level_severity);

end

title.@value: Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - vmw_esxi_title - Extract key/value pair

source.@value:
rule "Syslog - VMWARE ESXI - vmw_esxi_title - Extract key/value pair"

when
has_field("vmw_esxi_title")

then
set_fields(
		fields:
				key_value(
					value: to_string($message.vmw_esxi_title),
					trim_value_chars: "",
					trim_key_chars:"",
					delimiters:" ",
					kv_delimiters:"="
					)
		);
end
